content:
Here's the cleaned-up text:

Set Branding for the Channel Menu

Select the button colors, header background, and font in the menu to reflect your company’s brand identity on your website.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Channel Menu setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Channel Menu:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

Before you start, get your company’s brand color codes from the team that maintains your website. Select colors by entering the Hex code or RGB code or by selecting in the color picklist.

Here’s a side-by-side comparison of a Channel Menu before and after light branding. The button and header background colors were changed in Branding. The Header text was changed in Labels.

From the Channel Menu Settings page, select Edit for Branding. Follow the steps to customize your buttons:

Select Button and Button Icon colors. Add your Hex code, RGB code, or select a color in the picklist.
Use our default button and close icons, or add custom URLs to replace them.
Expand the Channel Menu Header and Background section and decide to Show header or not with a tick in the check box.
Pick colors for the header background and text, and set your Header Text Alignment in the picklist.
Add an optional Header Background Image URL or leave this blank for a solid color.
Customize the main panel with a Menu Background Color, Menu Text Color, Menu Text Hover Color, and Menu Background Hover Color.
Select Show lines between items if you want optional horizontal lines to appear between your menu items, and select a Horizontal Line Color.
Select a preferred font for your menu and choose a base font size.
Another option is to select Custom Font... at the bottom of the picklist. Type your Custom Font Family Name in the box and choose a font size. The font must be hosted on your web server.

Check your branding selections n the Preview window. Custom fonts and custom buttons don’t appear.
Save your changes.
NOTE If your Preview window is empty or missing a channel, return to your Menu Setup and check your selections.
NOTE Keep in mind that maximum header height is set to 75 pixels as you select the font size or add a custom background image URL.
NOTE Some fonts aren’t supported on mobile browsers. If you select a font that isn’t available for a mobile user, the browser’s default font is displayed.
title: Setting Up Channel Menu Branding in Service Cloud
